This paper focuses on object parsing and instance segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also incorporates a Conditional Random Field (CRF), which is a common tool in natural language processing (cs.CL) and image processing (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of supervised and semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
